==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thyrohyal
<hw>Thy`ro*hy"al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>One of the lower segments in the hyoid arch, often consolidated
with the body of the hyoid bone and forming one of its great horns, as
in man.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thyrohyoid</ent>⟦br⟧
